The world’s largest search engine, Google, has celebrated Nigeria on its website with a special doodle to commemorate the nation’s 60th Independence Anniversary on October 1. The doodle features the Nigerian green and white colours with a picture of a brown eagle standing with figure 60. A click on the doodle opens up another page where important facts about Nigeria and its history are displayed. To mark the Nigeria’s 59th Anniversary in 2019,the doodle showed a picture of Nigeria with Aso Rock at the background. A Google Doodle is a special, temporary alteration of the logo on Google’s homepages intended to commemorate holidays, events, achievements and notable historical figures. In January 2010 the first animated Doodle honored Sir Isaac Newton.